defaultThe TUC concurs with this view of the importance of industrial CCS. In 
defaultan increasingly carbon constrained world, considerable first mover advantages are available from the early development of industry CCS. As DECC points out, industrial facilities which are located close to other industries or power stations and storage site
defaults are more likely to be able to implement CCS if they can share transport and storage infrastructure.
