defaultA roadmap for coaldefaultA major potential benefit from CCS deployment
default will be to secure the long
default-
defaultterm future for UK coal mining
default and its 9,000 employees.
default 
defaultWithout investment in CCS there is no long term future for the UK coal industry. 
default 
defaultActions taken now to invest in CCS 
defaultand reform our electricity market can secure this core industry in a low carbon economy for the long term. Delays will drive investment and dependency on gas fired power without resolving the challenge of CO2 capture, whilst losing a once-only opportunity 
defaultfor global leadership in the vital CCS industry. 
defaultThe UK mines 
defaultin 2012 mined 
defaultover 1
default7
default million tonnes of coal a year, and 
defaultits 
defaultcoal power stations generate over 
default38%
default of the UK’s electricity
default 
defaultcompared with 
default28
default% from gas generators. At peak times, we turn to the e
defaultxceptional flexibility of coal power for up to 50% of our electricity supply. Coal 
defaultcurrently 
defaultdirectly provides over 
default5
default,000 jobs in deep and surface mines and ancillary functions, whilst coal power stations employ over 4,
default000
default staff, many in skilled quality em
defaultployment. 
defaultThe government should therefore develop a roadmap for UK coal mining alongside its EMR implementation plan, to provide security for UK coal investors and its workforce.
